## Natural vs Lab-Grown Diamond Guide for Anniversary Rings

| Factor | Natural Diamond | Lab-Grown Diamond |
|--------|----------------|-------------------|
| Appearance | Identical at same grade | Identical at same grade |
| Price | Higher | 30–70% lower |
| Resale value | Holds partial value | Minimal resale value |
| Quality grades | GIA/IGI certified | GIA/IGI certified |
| Right for | Investment-minded buyers, heirlooms | Buyers prioritizing size/budget |
| Wrong for | Budget-limited buyers who want more carat | Anyone expecting resale value |
| Review data | Riviera Pavé: 865 reviews | Riviera Pavé lab-grown: 20 reviews |

**The honest summary:** If this anniversary ring will be worn and kept, lab-grown saves meaningful money. If it's a potential heirloom or you might upgrade later, natural diamond preserves more value. Both options are real diamonds. Only one holds market value.

