## Who Should NOT Buy Anniversary Rings from Blue Nile

**Don't buy an anniversary ring without checking your existing ring stack.** Anniversary rings need to sit flush against your engagement ring and wedding band. Band width, profile height, and setting style all affect fit. Blue Nile's sizing guides help, but this is one purchase where having the rings in hand matters.

**Don't buy seven-stone or bezel designs with 0–1 reviews over $3,000 without calling first.** Several Seven Stone Bezel items in the $3,950–$19,490 range carry 0–1 reviews. At these prices, a call to Blue Nile to ask about current stock and quality specifics is worth five minutes.

**Don't buy lab-grown expecting resale value.** Lab-grown diamond prices continue to fall. A lab-grown anniversary ring bought today has minimal secondary market value. This is fine if you're keeping it — it's not fine if you view jewelry as an investment.

**Don't choose platinum if you're budget-sensitive.** Platinum variants are typically $200–$500 more than 14K gold equivalents on this page. Platinum is worth the premium for daily wear and longevity, but if budget is tight, 14K white gold rhodium-plated is a reasonable alternative.

**Don't size yourself based on your engagement ring.** Anniversary bands often fit differently than solitaire engagement rings. If you're unsure, Blue Nile's free ring sizer or a local jeweler's measurement is worth getting before ordering.

---

## What I Don't Love About Blue Nile Anniversary Rings

**1. The natural/lab toggle is too easy to miss.** Many buyers who price a ring on mobile never see the lab-grown option because it appears below the main price. This causes both overspending (buying natural when lab was fine) and underspending (accidentally buying lab-grown without understanding the resale implications). Blue Nile could do more to make this choice explicit at the top of every listing.

**2. Review counts thin out quickly above the Riviera Pavé.** The 865-review Riviera Pavé creates an illusion that the whole page is well-validated. In reality, most styles above $2,000 carry under 10 reviews. Buyers at those price points are working with less buyer-confirmation data than the page's dominant ring suggests.

**3. Diamond grade disclosure varies by collection.** The entry Riviera Pavé and Floating Diamond (older items) don't specify H-I/SI1-SI2 in the listing title. The 250th Anniversary Collection items do. Buyers comparing prices across the page may not realize they're comparing different grade specifications.

**4. No profile/height information for stacking.** Whether an anniversary ring stacks flush against an engagement ring depends on band height and profile — information Blue Nile doesn't provide upfront. This creates sizing uncertainty for buyers who own Blue Nile or other-brand engagement rings.

