## Frequently Asked Questions

### What is the most reviewed anniversary ring at Blue Nile?

The Riviera Pavé Diamond Ring — 865 verified reviews across variants in 14K white gold, yellow gold, rose gold, 18K yellow gold, and platinum. This is the most buyer-confirmed anniversary ring design by a wide margin on the entire page. Nothing else comes close.

### What is the Riviera Pavé setting?

A continuous band of small round diamonds set in a channel-like row with small prong tabs holding each stone. The diamonds appear to flow seamlessly around the band. It's understated enough to stack with engagement rings and statement enough to wear alone. Blue Nile's entry version starts at $980 in 18K yellow gold (1/6 ct).

### Should I choose natural or lab-grown diamonds for an anniversary ring?

Natural if you value long-term resale potential or want to leave an heirloom. Lab-grown if budget is your priority and you're keeping the ring. Both options look identical and come with GIA/IGI certification. The price difference is significant — the lab-grown Riviera Pavé at 1/2 ct costs $770 vs $1,280 for the natural 1/2 ct. The tradeoff is entirely about what you value.

### What carat weight should I choose for an anniversary ring?

1/6 ct to 1/4 ct is subtle and stackable — ideal if the ring will sit alongside an engagement ring. 1/2 ct is a visible statement, noticeable on its own. 3/4 ct to 1 ct is a bold everyday ring or a significant milestone gift. For comparison, the most-reviewed Riviera Pavé starts at 1/6 ct ($980) — its buyer confidence doesn't depend on carat size.

### What is the Floating Diamond design?

A ring where small diamonds appear to float above the band surface without visible prong settings from the top. The diamonds are held by minimal metal below, creating an airy, light effect different from the continuous pavé of the Riviera. It's 30% off in the 1/3 ct natural version ($770) with 177 reviews.

### What is French pavé?

A pavé technique where stones are set in angled cuts rather than straight channels, allowing more light to pass through from below each diamond. This creates more sparkle per stone than standard shared-prong pavé. Blue Nile's French Pavé Anniversary Ring starts at ~~$890~~ **$623** (30% off, 6 reviews) — a step up in brilliance from the Riviera Pavé at a similar price point.

### Do Blue Nile anniversary rings stack with engagement rings?

Most of Blue Nile's anniversary bands are designed to stack, but fit depends on band width and profile height. Contour-cut bands (like the Five Stone Shared Prong Contour) curve to sit flush against solitaire engagement rings. Straight bands (like the Riviera Pavé and Floating Diamond) stack best with straight-band engagement rings. Measure your current ring's profile height before ordering.

### What is the Seven Stone Bezel Oval ring?

A band with seven oval-cut diamonds each set in individual bezels (metal wrapping each stone completely). The bezel protects the diamond from catching and gives a modern, architectural look. Blue Nile carries this design in 14K white and yellow gold from 1 CTW ($3,950) to 3.5 CTW ($19,490). One review on each — new to the catalog.

### Is platinum worth the premium for an anniversary ring?

For daily wear: yes. Platinum is denser than gold, doesn't require rhodium re-plating, and is naturally hypoallergenic. For occasional wear: 14K white gold is a reasonable alternative at $200–$500 less per ring on this page. Platinum shows scratches as a patina rather than metal loss — some buyers prefer this. It develops a distinctive matte finish over time.

### What anniversary milestone is the Seven Stone ring for?

Seven-stone anniversary rings are traditionally associated with the 7th anniversary. However, they're also commonly given for 10th, 15th, 20th, and 25th anniversaries — the number of stones represents different meanings depending on tradition. Blue Nile's seven-stone designs work for any meaningful anniversary; the number of stones doesn't have to match the anniversary year.

### Can I stack a Blue Nile anniversary ring with a non-Blue Nile engagement ring?

Yes — ring stacking compatibility is about width, profile height, and shank shape, not brand. Blue Nile's Riviera Pavé and Floating Diamond bands are thin enough to stack with most engagement rings. The Seven Stone Bezel bands are wider (4–7mm) and may not sit flush against rings with wide shanks or prominent side stones.

### What is the return policy for Blue Nile anniversary rings?

Blue Nile offers a 30-day return policy on most rings. Engraved or customized items may not be returnable. Verify current policy at bluenile.com at time of purchase.

